# Security And Data Rules

- Never hardcode secrets, tokens, service keys, or private URLs in code or logs.
- Validate all external input at boundaries (Telegram payloads, API body/query, Sheets/Drive data).
- Use parameterized database queries only; never interpolate SQL manually.
- Do not expose internal errors to client UI; log technical details server-side.
- Keep access checks explicit: admin actions only for `adminTelegramIds`.

## Data Integrity

- Catalog sync must preserve MURU constraints: file naming `MUxxxx-N.webp`, exactly 2 images per product.
- Products with zero stock remain visible with "Под заказ" behavior.
- Payment remains disabled until explicit product approval.
- Any schema or mapping change requires backward-compatibility notes in implementation report.
